                                <div class="card custom-section p-4 mb-4 wow fadeInUp">
                                    <h4 class="section-title">📘 Terms Used</h4>
                                    <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>Price:</strong> Current trading price of the asset.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>Volume:</strong> Amount of transactions in a given time.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>Resistance Level:</strong> A level where price keeps failing to go higher.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>Support Level:</strong> A price level where price usually bounces up.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>Moving Average (MA):</strong> A calculation used to analyze data points by creating averages over a specific time period. It helps smooth out price data and identify trends.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>RSI:</strong> A momentum oscillator that measures the speed and change of price movements. RSI values range from 0 to 100, indicating overbought or oversold conditions.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>MACD:</strong> A trend-following momentum indicator that shows the relationship between two moving averages of a security’s price.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>Bollinger Bands:</strong> A volatility indicator that consists of a middle band (SMA) and two outer bands that represent standard deviations from the middle band.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-corner-down-right-line mt-0 mr-2 ml-2 text-success"></i><strong>Upper Band:</strong> This is the middle band (SMA) plus a set number of standard deviations (usually 2). It represents the upper limit of price volatility.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-corner-down-right-line mt-0 mr-2 ml-2 text-success"></i><strong>Middle Band (SMA):</strong> This is a simple moving average (SMA) of the asset's price, typically set to 20 periods.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-corner-down-right-line mt-0 mr-2 ml-2 text-success"></i><strong>Lower Band:</strong> This is the middle band (SMA) minus the same number of standard deviations (usually 2). It represents the lower limit of price volatility.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-success"></i><strong>On-Balance Volume (OBV):</strong> A technical analysis indicator that uses volume flow to predict changes in stock price.</li>



                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Breakout:</strong> Price moving above resistance or below support.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Capitulation:</strong> Panic sell after heavy drop. Possible reversal point.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Bull Trap:</strong> Fake breakout upward to trick traders.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Trend:</strong> The general direction in which the market or asset is moving, either upwards, downwards, or sideways.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Volume Profile:</strong> A charting tool that shows the amount of a particular asset that was traded at different price levels over a set period.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Fibonacci Retracement:</strong> A tool used to identify potential support and resistance levels based on the key Fibonacci numbers, often used to predict price reversals.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Candlestick Patterns:</strong> A charting technique used to visualize the price movements of an asset over a set time period, helping traders predict market direction.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>ATR:</strong> A volatility indicator that measures the degree of price movement, helping traders assess the risk in a particular asset.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Stochastic Oscillator:</strong> A momentum indicator that compares a particular closing price to a range of prices over a certain period of time.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Parabolic SAR:</strong> A trend-following indicator that determines potential points where an asset might reverse direction.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Divergence:</strong> A situation where the price of an asset moves in the opposite direction to an indicator, potentially signaling a reversal.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>VWAP:</strong> The average price of an asset, weighted by volume, used to measure the true average price.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Liquidity:</strong> The ease with which an asset can be bought or sold without causing a significant impact on its price.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Order Book Depth:</strong> A tool that shows the current orders (buy/sell) in the market at various price levels, indicating market depth.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Delta (Price Change):</strong> The rate of change of an asset's price, typically shown as a percentage.</li>
                                        <li><i class="ri-arrow-right-box-fill mt-0 mr-2 text-danger"> </i><strong>Sentiment Analysis:</strong> The process of analyzing market sentiment (bullish or bearish) based on news, social media, and other sources to determine price movement.</li>
                                    </ul>

